  - Lairs: Demolition squad
- Fix particle effects
  x Shrine-blowup effect (rework, simplify and speedup)
  - Lightning mage static discharge (speedup/rework)
  - Lightning mage lightning bolt (make more distinctive)
x Fix prisoner hostility threeissues (with Revgen)
- Vaults pt 2
  - Add number of vaults defeated to scoresheet
    - Some kind of mechanism to "know" when player has truly defeated vault,
      or just opened it and ran away like a coward.
  - Remove regular monsters from vaults
    - Iron vaults: entirely remove?
      - Alternatively, mix of bone rats mobs and weak constructs
    - Dobalene vaults: should contain ONLY constructs
    - Golden rooms: bunch of undead.
    - Marble: theming & monsters are okay.
  - Marble vaults: pure gold cloak prefab
  - Marble vaults: ornate gold armor prefab (rare, usually in unholy temple)
  - Marble vaults: tactic rooms, combat dummies, skeletal arbalists
  - Armory room: anti-night-creature variant
    - Potion of extermination
    - See glow potion buf item below
  - Dobalene rooms
  - Ensure all vault types are sufficiently rare (can stuff it into map
    prefab frequency analysis)
  - Level "feels" message when entering.
    - Golden: "you feel death in the air."
    - Dobalene: "you recall a squad of constructs passing this way."
    - Marble: "this floor is unusually silent."
- Living dungeon
  - Execution sessions
  - Spire cleanup
    - Engineer shows up to clean and oil spires
    - Engineer shows up to repair spires (just theater, spires aren't actually broken)
  - Scheduled prisoner transport
    - Thoughts to make this viable: instead of making the act of dragging
      prisoner a passive thing that happens automatically when the mob moves,
      make it an active thing (i.e. explicitely calling dragPrisoner() in
      hauler's AI); and tickEnv will automatically release prisoner if its
      guardian isn't adjacent. Yes, prisoner escapes far more often, but at
      least it's less fragile and fewer unpredictable situations
- Night Creatures, part three
  - Decreased rep for:
    - Killing NC
    - Throwing fire/illuminations potions at NC
  - NC travel: "hop" (teleport) from one dark tile to another, only walking
    if the next dark tile is too far away
  - Items
    - Item to find and reveal lairs
    - Rare, limited-use evocable to "destroy" lair, removing all slade +
      breaking door + tele'ing NCs (66% chance) to another lair (animation:
      like Cogmind gamma burst trap)
    - Make illumination/glow potions useful for raiding lairs
      - Aggroes all NC in vicinity
      - Corona/glowing damages NC, causes fleeing if wounded
      - Increased rarity + novel prefab for 7/ and 8/
    - Special, rare NC-blasting items in Shrine/Necropolis/Crypt/Lab
      - Destroys slade tiles, aggroes all NC, instant -10 rep
  - Armory dedicated to NC destruction
    - Many of above items
    - Poster that explains how to do this
  - Exterminator events
  - Angel ambush/revenge event (see notes)
- Necropolis floor
  x Modify level data and spawn files
  - New monsters:
    - Vile protector
    - Hornblende statues
    - Schalenblende statues(?)
    - Pitchblende statues
    - Skeletal arbalists
  - Garrison inset prefabs
  - Ability to gain MP/HP somehow (or not? maybe that's the challenge :P)
  - Prefabs:
    - Paralysed+dormant arbalists/blademasters behind bars
    - Arbalists shooting at targets (DM observing)
    - Blademasters practicing formations (DM observing)
    - DM failing to resurrect dead revgen, cinder brute
  - Swollen growth, osseous ash, deathly weepers (see ~/doc/notes/necropolis.txt)
  - Gravestones (see ~/doc/notes/necropolis.txt)
